REALLY IMPORTANT TO US: Kickstarter LINK IN BIO:
Flagship is back! For the first time in over a decade we are once again an independent band and we have our hearts set on making our third full length album this spring. This means that for the first time in a long time we have the opportunity to invite our community, which we have all built together over the years, to join us in creating something beautiful together. This means that we need our community to invest and take ownership in this album along side of us. This will be OUR album. I personally couldn’t be more excited about this chance to create, under new and unfamiliar circumstances, an album that brings Flagship back to it’s roots musically, but also to make it new...to apply all of the lessons learned and skills acquired since we released our very first album. I think this approach of revisiting our original sound with a fresh perspective will help us create our best collection of songs ever. I won’t say who will be recording in this group yet, but I’m certain that our fans will be excited when they see who will be working in the studio on this one. We’ve got a few familiar faces and a few new additions and its going to be just right. As most of you know Kickstarters are all or nothing. If we don’t hit our mark of $22,500 we won’t receive any of the funds. So you know when i say that we can’t do this without you...it’s the truth. We need our community to share this Kickstarter link with everyone that you know who appreciates and supports the arts. You can text it. You can share it on IG, TikTok, Twitter, Facebook, email...etc. If Flagship has ever touched your life in a positive way or if our music has moved you we need you now. If you’ve appreciated my openness and my commitment to always make time for this community...we need you. We’ve given ourselves 30 days to achieve this goal and I have every reason to believe that we will meet our mark. We sincerely couldn’t be more excited about this opportunity to create our best work with YOU. We’ve already got over 25 demos and this one is going to be special. Let’s make something that will stand the test of time.

“I am a fool now for you.” One of the first good songs I wrote. A reminder of what you’ll be investing in via the kickstarter in our bio. We are at 9% with 24 days left to reach our goal. This could very well be it for me and us musically if we don’t meet our minimum goal. We need you to show up now….so that we can continue to do what we do well. Please step up…at least for the equivalent of a coffee…this is just me trying to remember an old song…the new ones are…what you want. “I feel it coming, feel it coming, all the walls are caving in…I know you’re coming, I feel you’re coming…all the walls are falling in.”
CRUCIAL…If you’ve cared for me or @flagship please take a few minutes to listen. It’d mean a lot. Kickstarter link in bio. 🙏🫶🙏
“Fever” An old one, but one of my favorite love songs I’ve written. p.s. We’re at 40% on the kickstarter and a day away from being at the half point mark…we’re a bit behind. Find the link in my bio.

“Gold and Silver” …This song is about how the wealthy take from the poor and make it nearly impossible to take care of the ones/ one that you love. We are 9% behind where we should be on the kickstarter at the halfway point (15 days left) please find the link in the bio.

I’ve put this on stories before but not as a post. I don’t know if I had or have ever been happier on a stage than I was in Paris for the first time. For some reason playing in Paris meant the world to me. I watch this and I want to run through a wall. Song name, “Wagon.”

There are four days left to go on our kickstarter…If you want to be a part of a miracle please find the kickstarter link in the bio. Haha. Like I said in the video…I just want to express my gratitude for all of you who have  pitched in. We raised a good amount of funds. If we do in fact fail to meet our minimum in the next four days, everyone who donated through Kickstarter will get a refund…If you sent funds directly to me via cashapp or Venmo…I will hold on to that for the next step. We will get back to the drawing board if we fail, and we will find a way to bring this music to life…it will happen, and we’ll be in touch as to how. Much love!
“Kid all day,” live from Paris part 2…find link in bio to bring this back.

“The fool,” ending (from Paris) We would close all of our shows with this song for a long time and normally by then I was pretty exhausted, but it was always just so powerful to let loose and go as hard as we could go at the end…I’ve only broken one guitar in my life and it was at the end of this song at a show in Raleigh…and I knew I messed up because it was a really nice guitar of mine…I threw it head down and it shattered…I don’t regret it though…something like that is entirely cathartic…anyways there are about 3 days left on the Kickstarter…it’s the miracle time…if not we’ll be in touch on what’s next. -D

Since most people seemed to like this…I’m going to post this cover of “Only Son of the Ladiesman.” 2 days left on our kickstarter…it’ll take a miracle, but I’m still in it…we’re still in it. Link in bio.
“Life Underwater” (from Paris) one day left on the kickstarter. Link in bio.
Special announcement in the second half. Our Indiegogo is live…find the link in my bio. Let’s make this happen! 🫶🫶🫶

We raised $10,600 last month…as you know we weren’t able to keep it because we didn’t hit our mark. All that we ask now is that you come back via the indiegogo.com fundraiser link in our bio section and do whatever you already did last month…as you weren’t charged for the previous month. We are grateful for what you did last month and we just need you to show up and do it one more time. This one will count regardless of if we hit our goal. Thank you. Much love 🫶

No lie, how I test my songs…if I can cry to them, or if I can dance to them…this is clearly the latter. p.s. Like it or hate it…I’m happy either way.

MOOD…My life has been a rollercoaster since 2020…like a lot of people I experienced loss on a scale that I wasn’t prepared for. It’s difficult to build something for so long and see it dissolve so fast…but hey, we all experience it at least once on some level. I’m doing my very best to rebuild with my close friends…but we’re on our own now, and while there are pros to that, there are also cons…as with anything. I need your help. I need you to go to the link in my bio and do whatever you can…even if it’s just $10…it all counts. I don’t want to stop bringing you music and I don’t know how to quit. I’m so grateful for those of you who have jumped in with me. Let’s create something together. You can own this with me. It’s my purpose, I’ve known it for a long time. Help make it possible. I promise I will make it worth the while. XO

My story: 
I was going to go into great detail about the deep lows that I gradually hit over my three years in Nashville…the years leading up to my second genuine and legitimate sobriety date, which came on June the 11th of this year. I will say that had I not been such a danger to myself and moved back to NC (with the help of my family) when I did that I very well may have died had I continued to drink as I was. I was lost. I was angry…I had never known such anger. I drank alone at the end and I didn’t want to wake up. I had lost it all, or at least that’s the lie that played over and over in my head. My life was over, my music wasted, my friends gone, and this tormented me night and day until I was nothing. As many of you know I was sober from 2018 through 2021. I moved to Nashville in 2021 and it didn’t take long for me to give in to what started as a little whisper…saying “you’re not an alcoholic, you just needed to dry out for a few years.” Long story short I went into a nose dive for all to see…I didn’t try to hide it... When I was sober for those 2 years and 6 months I refused to participate in any program or community…I insisted on staying sober alone and it failed. Now that I know and have fully accepted that I am an alcoholic through and through…I have found a community, a program, and something bigger than myself to believe in. It has saved my life. Instead of sharing the details of my downward spiral I will share with you that I have taken back my power. I have taken back my dignity. I have taken back my soul, and I have surrendered my will to something much greater than me. I am healthy and strong. I had a lot of help, but in the end I had to do the work…this work takes place everyday. I will take back my music career and I will chase it like never before. I will go further than I could’ve imagined with the help of my higher power, my family, and my friends. I will see my dreams come true. I will act in movies, shows, etc. Not because I’m special or better, but because it’s what I choose. I will be grateful for every single day that I wake up with love in my heart for myself and for others. (Continued in comments).

10 years! It’s been ten years since we released our first full length album. In celebration of this milestone I’ve added three bonus songs at the tail end across all platforms…”Native on the Run” is my favorite. Today is also bandcamp Friday…which means the artists get 100% of purchases today. Hit the link in my bio to purchase this new extended version of the album. Also, added an extra song to our Blackbush Ep…I think you’ll enjoy these.

I’ve felt “it” forever…I remember noticing “it” for the first time as a child when my stepdad brought me to do “inner city ministry.” I felt “it”deeply then, as I do now…We would rake leaves and repair beat up homes. “It” helped shape who I am, and I’m grateful to my stepfather for exposing me to “it” at an early age. “It” is a deep connection and love for broken people, places, and things. That is where my heart is, and where my music is…which are one and the same. That is where you will find me.

Sober, learning, unlearning, constructing, deconstructing, becoming…
